<subSubSection id="B7601F4D7E3832BADC78B93610BF1BDE" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="FC662BEA257CBFF543C19F0B7282DBB6" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="66130B2A5F43A3352007FAEC9650C453" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Differs from 
<taxonomicName id="20BF1FD9796CC9C58CC542C64BD2FF2C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sanchez-vegae">
<emphasis id="E747FFCBD5DEA6A3A5C28565B9C3A2B0" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Solanum sanchez-vegae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
S. Knapp in bearing tufts of dendritic trichomes in the vein axils of leaf undersides and elongate, densely pubescent buds; differs from 
<taxonomicName id="5F69B95CD9F6E33FA0532EC8032DBEB4" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laxum">
<emphasis id="2A404693A8E6CDFE7C53BBF06D631FE5" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Solanum laxum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Spreng. in having shiny upper leaf surfaces, dendritic trichomes rather than simple trichomes in the vein axils of leaf undersides, and densely pubescent buds.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A34777E4F3272F429C03A95D028538E9" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="type">
<paragraph id="022D2F20BA291AE186C1B5CA74F303DA" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="557A6DD86E236A6DDFAA185188C09EE3" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
